{"title_page": "Kevin Collins (American actor)", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| image = Kevin_Collins_2008.jpg\n| imagesize = 215px\n| caption = Collins with director, [[Jamil Dehlavi]], at the 2008 [[South Asian International Film Festival ]]\n| birth_name = Kevin Michael Collins\n| name = Kevin Collins\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1972|3|17}}\n| birth_place = [[Trenton, New Jersey]]\n| occupation = [[Actor]], [[voice actor]]\n| years active = 2004-present\n}}\n'''Kevin Michael Collins''' (born March 17, 1972 in [[Trenton, New Jersey]]) is an American-Irish stage and screen actor of [[Irish people|Irish]]-[[Italian people|Italian]] descent.\n\nCollins is an alumnus of [[the University of St. Michael's College|St. Michael's College]] at the [[University of Toronto]] and a graduate of the [[National Theatre School of Canada]] and the [[Ecole de Mime Corporel Dramatique]] in [[London]]. He was a member of the Irish company [[Blue Raincoat]] and of the London-based [[corporeal mime]] company [[Theatre de l'Ange Fou]].\n\nIn theatre he has worked in the [[West End theatre|West End]],<ref name=\"http://www.whatsonstage.com\">{{cite news|title=Ringwald Confirms as West End's New Sally|publisher=www.whatsonstage.com|accessdate=2010-12-10|url=http://www.whatsonstage.com/news/theatre/london/E8821084444518/Ringwald+Confirms+as+West+End's+New+Sally,+2+Jun.html|archive-url=https://archive.today/20130209040827/http://www.whatsonstage.com/news/theatre/london/E8821084444518/Ringwald+Confirms+as+West+End's+New+Sally,+2+Jun.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=2013-02-09|first=Terri|last=Paddock|date=2004-05-13}}</ref> with the [[Peter Hall Company]], and off-Broadway, most notably at the Irish Repertory Theatre.<ref name=\"www.nytimes.com\">{{cite news| title=Theater Review - It\u2019s Yeats Country. Do You Know Where Your Soul Is?|newspaper=[[New York Times]]|accessdate=2009-04-28|url=http://theater2.nytimes.com/2009/04/21/theater/reviews/21yeat.html | first=Charles | last=Isherwood | date=2009-04-21}}</ref>   On film he has appeared in ''[[Everybody's Fine (2009 film)|Everybody's Fine]]'', ''[[Baby Mama (film)|Baby Mama]]'', [[Jamil Dehlavi]]'s ''[[Infinite Justice (film)|Infinite Justice]]'' and ''[[Munich (film)|Munich]]'', directed by [[Steven Spielberg]]. His television appearances include ''[[Unforgettable (2011 TV series)|Unforgettable]]'', ''[[Law & Order]]'', ''[[All My Children]]'', ''[[Gossip Girl (TV series)|Gossip Girl]]'', ''[[Person of Interest (TV series)|Person of Interest]]'' and ''[[The Blacklist (TV series)|The Black List]]''.<ref name=IMDb>{{cite web| title=IMDb|accessdate=2009-02-23|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm1944404/}}</ref>\n\nCollins is also a voiceover artist whose voice is regularly heard in national ad campaigns in the United States, Canada, the UK and Ireland. As a voice actor, his credits include work for RT\u00c9 and BBC radio drama, and documentary narration.\n\nHe also acted in ''[[Just Cause 3]]'', taking the main role as Rico Rodriguez.\n\n==Filmography==\n===Film===\n* ''[[Baby Mama (film)|Baby Mama]]'' as Rick\n* ''[[Infinite Justice (film)|Infinite Justice]]'' as Arnold Silverman\n*[[Munich (film)|Munich]]\n\n===Television===\n* ''[[Guiding Light]]'' as Dr. Brandon Cohen\n\n===Videogame===\n*''[[DC Universe Online]]'' - [[Thomas Wayne]]\n*''[[Just Cause 3]]'' - Rico Rodriguez\n*''[[Street Racing Syndicate|SRS: Street Racing Syndicate]] -\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.kevincollins.com/ Official website: www.kevincollins.com]\n*{{IMDb name|id=1944404|name=Kevin Collins}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20071022043624/http://voiceovers.co.uk/kevin.collins/ Voiceover clips]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Collins, Kevin}}\n[[Category:1972 births]]\n[[Category:American male stage actors]]\n[[Category:American male film actors]]\n[[Category:American male television actors]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| image = Kevin_Collins_2008.jpg\n| imagesize = 215px\n| caption = Collins with director, [[Jamil Dehlavi]], at the 2008 [[South Asian International Film Festival ]]\n| birth_name = Kevin Michael Collins\n| name = Kevin Collins\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1972|3|17}}\n| birth_place = [[Trenton, New Jersey]]\n| occupation = [[Actor]], [[voice actor]]\n| years active = 2004-present\n}}\n'''Kevin Michael Collins''' (born March 17, 1972 in [[Trenton, New Jersey]]) is an American-Irish stage and screen actor of [[Irish]]-[[Italian people|Italian]] descent.\n\nCollins is an alumnus of [[the University of St. Michael's College|St. Michael's College]] at the [[University of Toronto]] and a graduate of the [[National Theatre School of Canada]] and the [[Ecole de Mime Corporel Dramatique]] in [[London]]. He was a member of the Irish company [[Blue Raincoat]] and of the London-based [[corporeal mime]] company [[Theatre de l'Ange Fou]].\n\nIn theatre he has worked in the [[West End theatre|West End]],<ref name=\"http://www.whatsonstage.com\">{{cite news|title=Ringwald Confirms as West End's New Sally|publisher=www.whatsonstage.com|accessdate=2010-12-10|url=http://www.whatsonstage.com/news/theatre/london/E8821084444518/Ringwald+Confirms+as+West+End's+New+Sally,+2+Jun.html|archive-url=https://archive.today/20130209040827/http://www.whatsonstage.com/news/theatre/london/E8821084444518/Ringwald+Confirms+as+West+End's+New+Sally,+2+Jun.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=2013-02-09|first=Terri|last=Paddock|date=2004-05-13}}</ref> with the [[Peter Hall Company]], and off-Broadway, most notably at the Irish Repertory Theatre.<ref name=\"www.nytimes.com\">{{cite news| title=Theater Review - It\u2019s Yeats Country. Do You Know Where Your Soul Is?|newspaper=[[New York Times]]|accessdate=2009-04-28|url=http://theater2.nytimes.com/2009/04/21/theater/reviews/21yeat.html | first=Charles | last=Isherwood | date=2009-04-21}}</ref>   On film he has appeared in ''[[Everybody's Fine (2009 film)|Everybody's Fine]]'', ''[[Baby Mama (film)|Baby Mama]]'', [[Jamil Dehlavi]]'s ''[[Infinite Justice (film)|Infinite Justice]]'' and ''[[Munich (film)|Munich]]'', directed by [[Steven Spielberg]]. His television appearances include ''[[Unforgettable (2011 TV series)|Unforgettable]]'', ''[[Law & Order]]'', ''[[All My Children]]'', ''[[Gossip Girl (TV series)|Gossip Girl]]'', ''[[Person of Interest (TV series)|Person of Interest]]'' and ''[[The Blacklist (TV series)|The Black List]]''.<ref name=IMDb>{{cite web| title=IMDb|accessdate=2009-02-23|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm1944404/}}</ref>\n\nCollins is also a voiceover artist whose voice is regularly heard in national ad campaigns in the United States, Canada, the UK and Ireland. As a voice actor, his credits include work for RT\u00c9 and BBC radio drama, and documentary narration.\n\nHe also acted in ''[[Just Cause 3]]'', taking the main role as Rico Rodriguez.\n\n==Filmography==\n===Film===\n* ''[[Baby Mama (film)|Baby Mama]]'' as Rick\n* ''[[Infinite Justice (film)|Infinite Justice]]'' as Arnold Silverman\n*[[Munich (film)|Munich]]\n\n===Television===\n* ''[[Guiding Light]]'' as Dr. Brandon Cohen\n\n===Videogame===\n*''[[DC Universe Online]]'' - [[Thomas Wayne]]\n*''[[Just Cause 3]]'' - Rico Rodriguez\n*''[[Street Racing Syndicate|SRS: Street Racing Syndicate]] -\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.kevincollins.com/ Official website: www.kevincollins.com]\n*{{IMDb name|id=1944404|name=Kevin Collins}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20071022043624/http://voiceovers.co.uk/kevin.collins/ Voiceover clips]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Collins, Kevin}}\n[[Category:1972 births]]\n[[Category:American male stage actors]]\n[[Category:American male film actors]]\n[[Category:American male television actors]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "name_user": "Rodw", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguating links toIrish(link changed toIrish people) usingDisamAssist.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kevin_Collins_(American_actor)"}
{"title_page": "Deputy commissioner", "text_new": "{{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}}\nA '''deputy commissioner''' is a [[police]], [[income tax]] or administrative official in many different countries. The rank is commonplace in police forces of [[Commonwealth of Nations|Commonwealth]] countries, usually ranking below the Commissioner.\n\n==Australia==\nIn all Australian police forces, deputy commissioner is the rank directly below that of [[commissioner]] and senior to the rank of [[assistant commissioner]]. In all forces, excepting the New South Wales Police Force where the insignia is crossed and wreathed tipstaves surmounted by a crown, the same insignia as that of a [[lieutenant-general]] in the army, the insignia is a diamond (or a star, in the case of the Victoria Police), the same as that of a [[major-general]] in the army.\n\n==Bangladesh==\nThe Deputy Commissioner (popularly abbreviated to \"DC\") or [[Deputy Commissioner (Bangladesh)|District Magistrate]] is the executive head of the [[districts of Bangladesh|district]], an administrative sub-unit of a [[divisions of Bangladesh|division]]. The deputy commissioners are appointed by the government from a [[ministries of Bangladesh|Deputy Secretary]] of [[Bangladesh Civil Service|BCS]] Administration Cadre.The [[Deputy Commissioner of Taxes]] or the DCT is the Income Tax officer who is an Income Tax authority according to the Income Tax Ordinance, 1984. Deputy Commissioner of Taxes are basically officers of [[Bangladesh Civil Service|BCS]] Taxation Cadre. DCT includes Assistant Commissioner of Taxes as well.\n\n==Hong Kong==\n[[Hong Kong Police Force]] have three types of DCs:\n\n* Operations\n* Management\n* I don't know this one but you can get from outside Wikipedia.\n\n== India and Pakistan ==\nThe '''deputy commissioner''' or [[district magistrate]] is the executive head of a district, an administrative sub-unit of a state. The '''district magistrates''' are entrusted with overall responsibility for law and order, implementation of government schemes and are also authorised to hear revenue cases pertaining to the district.  A district magistrate is also authorised to collect Land Revenue and is therefore also referred as a [[district collector|collector]] (revenue) and also to control encroachment of government land in the district. In India officers of [[Indian Administrative Service]] cadre are appointed this office and in Pakistan usually the Pakistan Administrative Service, formally known as [[District Management Group]], cadre of the [[Central Superior Services]]  or officers of Provincial Management Services erstwhile Provincial Civil Services are appointed to this office.\n\n== Papua New Guinea ==\n\nIn the [[Royal Papua New Guinea Constabulary]], there are three  Deputy Commissioners. They report to the [[Police Commissioner]] and are in charge of all Police Duties by directing their respective [[Assistant Commissioner|ACP's]].<ref>news.pngfacts.com/2016/02/australian-alan-scott-appointed-deputy.html</ref>\n\n* Operations\n* Administration\n* Training, Reform and [[Asia Pacific Economic Cooperation|APEC]]\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n==See also==\n*[[Deputy commissioner of police (disambiguation)]]\n*[[Deputy commissioner (India)]]\n\n[[Category:Police ranks]]\n\n{{Gov-job-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}}\nA '''deputy commissioner''' is a [[police]], [[income tax]] or administrative official in many different countries. The rank is commonplace in police forces of [[Commonwealth of Nations|Commonwealth]] countries, usually ranking below the Commissioner.\n\n==Australia==\nIn all Australian police forces, deputy commissioner is the rank directly below that of [[commissioner]] and senior to the rank of [[assistant commissioner]]. In all forces, excepting the New South Wales Police Force where the insignia is crossed and wreathed tipstaves surmounted by a crown, the same insignia as that of a [[lieutenant-general]] in the army, the insignia is a diamond (or a star, in the case of the Victoria Police), the same as that of a [[major-general]] in the army.\n\n==Bangladesh==\nThe Deputy Commissioner (popularly abbreviated to \"DC\") or [[Deputy Commissioner (Bangladesh)|District Magistrate]] is the executive head of the [[districts of Bangladesh|district]], an administrative sub-unit of a [[divisions of Bangladesh|division]]. The deputy commissioners are appointed by the government from a [[ministries of Bangladesh|Deputy Secretary]] of [[Bangladesh Civil Service|BCS]] Administration Cadre.The [[Deputy Commissioner of Taxes]] or the DCT is the Income Tax officer who is an Income Tax authority according to the Income Tax Ordinance, 1984. Deputy Commissioner of Taxes are basically officers of [[Bangladesh Civil Service|BCS]] Taxation Cadre. DCT includes Assistant Commissioner of Taxes as well.\n\n==Hong Kong==\n[[Hong Kong Police Force]] have three types of DCs:\n\n* Operations\n* Management\n* I don't know this one but you can get from outside Wikipedia.\n\n== India and Pakistan ==\nThe '''deputy commissioner''' or [[district magistrate]] is the executive head of a district, an administrative sub-unit of a state. The '''district magistrates''' are entrusted with overall responsibility for law and order, implementation of government schemes and is also authorised to hear revenue cases pertaining to the district.  District magistrate is also authorised to collect Land Revenue and is therefore also referred [[district collector|collector]] (revenue) and also to control encroachment of government land in the district. In India officers of [[Indian Administrative Service]] cadre are appointed this office and in Pakistan usually the Pakistan Administrative Service, formally known as [[District Management Group]], cadre of the [[Central Superior Services]]  or officers of Provincial Management Services erstwhile Provincial Civil Services are appointed to this office.\n\n== Papua New Guinea ==\n\nIn the [[Royal Papua New Guinea Constabulary]], there are three  Deputy Commissioners. They report to the [[Police Commissioner]] and are in charge of all Police Duties by directing their respective [[Assistant Commissioner|ACP's]].<ref>news.pngfacts.com/2016/02/australian-alan-scott-appointed-deputy.html</ref>\n\n* Operations\n* Administration\n* Training, Reform and [[Asia Pacific Economic Cooperation|APEC]]\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n==See also==\n*[[Deputy commissioner of police (disambiguation)]]\n*[[Deputy commissioner (India)]]\n\n[[Category:Police ranks]]\n\n{{Gov-job-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Amiwikieditor", "label": "safe", "comment": "Fixed grammar", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Deputy_commissioner"}
{"title_page": "Solo Leveling", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{italic title|noerror|string=Solo Leveling|all=yes}}\n{{Infobox novel\n|name       = Solo Leveling\n|author     = Chu-Gong\n|language   = Korean\n|country    = South Korea\n|genre      = Action, Fantasy\n|published  = Papyrus, [[KakaoPage]]\n|pub_date   = February 14, 2014; February 17, 2017 \u2013 October 10, 2018\n|media_type = Novel\n|isbn       = 1170336663\n}}\n{{Infobox manhwa\n| name_2       = Solo Leveling\n| image        = Solo Leveling Webtoon.png\n| hangul       = \ub098 \ud63c\uc790\ub9cc \ub808\ubca8\uc5c5\n| romanized    = Na Honjaman Level-up\n| genre        = Action, Fantasy\n| Adaptation   = \n| author       = Chu-Gong\n| illustrator  = Hyeon-Gun, Jang Sung-Rak\n| publisher    = D&C Media<!--The publisher for webtoon in print is D&C Media (\ub514\uc564\uc528\ubbf8\ub514\uc5b4). DO NOT use Kakao as the publisher.-->\n| magazine     = {{ubl|[[KakaoPage]] (South Korea)|[[Piccoma]] (Japan)}}\n| first        = 2018\n| firstmo      = March 4,\n| last         = 2020\n| volumes      = 2\n| chapter_list = \n| related      = \n}}\n'''Solo Leveling''' ({{Korean|hangul=\ub098 \ud63c\uc790\ub9cc \ub808\ubca8\uc5c5|rr=Na Honjaman Level-up|labels=yes}}) is a South [[Korean language|Korean]] novel written by Chu-Gong. It was serialized in Papyrus and later in [[Kakao]]'s media platform [[KakaoPage]] and concluded with 14 volumes and 270 chapters.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ipapyrus.co.kr/?document_srl=2545847|script-title=ko: :::\uafc8\uacfc \ud76c\ub9dd\uc774 \uc0b4\uc544\uc788\ub294 \ud30c\ud53c\ub8e8\uc2a4::: - \ub098 \ud63c\uc790\ub9cc \ub808\ubca8\uc5c5|website=Papyrus|access-date=August 5, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://page.kakao.com/home?seriesId=48787313|script-title=ko:\ub098 \ud63c\uc790\ub9cc \ub808\ubca8\uc5c5 [\uc644\uacb0]|last=\ucd94\uacf5|website=KakaoPage|language=ko|access-date=August 5, 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe webtoon adaptation has been serialized in KakaoPage since March 4, 2018, illustrated by Hyeon-gun and Jang Sung-Rak.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://page.kakao.com/home?seriesId=50866481|script-title=ko:\ub098 \ud63c\uc790\ub9cc \ub808\ubca8\uc5c5 [\ub3c5\uc810\uc5f0\uc7ac]|website=KakaoPage|language=ko|access-date=August 5, 2019}}</ref> The individual chapters collected and published by D&C Media into two volumes as of April 2020. ''Solo Leveling'' has been translated to many languages by way of [[fan translations]].\n\n== Plot ==\nSince a portal connecting our world to a world full of monsters and creatures of all kinds appeared, some people have acquired powers and the ability to hunt them: they are called hunters. The protagonist of the story, Sung Jin-Woo, is the weakest of the rank E hunters and barely stronger than a normal human. He is nicknamed by his fellow hunters as \"the weakest\". One day, he and other hunters find themselves trapped in an extremely dangerous dungeon, and only a few of them survive and manage to escape. Sung Jin-Woo himself hardly survives and is the only one who completes all the trials in this dungeon. He then turns into a \"player\" who can now see an interface showing him quests. Will he succeed in becoming the most powerful hunter?\n\nThe manhwa depicts how the weakest of all the hunters grows to become the strongest there is. Hunter Sung-Woo likes clearing dungeons alone and have gained tremendous strength and magic powers in the process. The Ant arc just finished and Sung Jin-Woo was able to defeat the Ant king without even using his full strength. The main antagonist of the manhwa seems to be a demon who is working from the shadows and we expect him to be the last and final boss in the journey of hunter Sung Jin-Woo leveling up.\n\n== Media ==\n<!--=== Novel volumes ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n!Vol.\n!Chapters\n|-\n|1\n|1 ~ 22\n|-\n|2\n|22 ~ 45\n|-\n|3\n|46 ~ 64\n|-\n|4\n|65 ~ 82\n|-\n|5\n|83 ~ 101\n|-\n|6\n|102 ~ 119\n|-\n|7\n|120 ~ 138\n|-\n|8\n|139 ~ 155\n|-\n|9\n|156 ~ 174\n|-\n|10\n|175 ~ 192\n|-\n|11\n|193 ~ 211\n|-\n|12\n|211 ~ 228\n|-\n|13\n|229 ~ 248\n|-\n|14\n|249 ~ 270\n|}\n-->\n===Manhwa===\n''Solo Leveling'' was launched in Kakao's webtoon platform [[KakaoPage]] on March 4, 2010. Its first [[trade paperback (comics)|collected volume]] was released by D&C Media on September 26, 2019.\n\n====Volume list====\n{{Graphic novel list/header\n| OneLanguage     = yes\n| Language        = Korean\n| Width           = 75%\n}}\n{{Graphic novel list\n| VolumeNumber    = 01\n| RelDate         = September 26, 2019<ref name=\"vol1\">{{cite web|url=https://book.naver.com/bookdb/book_detail.nhn?bid=15407921|script-title=ko:\ub098 \ud63c\uc790\ub9cc \ub808\ubca8\uc5c5 1|website=[[Naver|Naver Book Database]]|language=ko|access-date=April 23, 2020}}</ref>\n| ISBN            = 979-1-18-932029-4\n| LicensedRelDate =\n| LicensedISBN    =\n| ChapterList     =\n}}\n{{Graphic novel list\n| VolumeNumber    = 02\n| RelDate         = January 30, 2020<ref name=\"vol2\">{{cite web|url=https://book.naver.com/bookdb/book_detail.nhn?bid=16122656|script-title=ko:\ub098 \ud63c\uc790\ub9cc \ub808\ubca8\uc5c5 2|website=[[Naver|Naver Book Database]]|language=ko|access-date=April 23, 2020}}</ref>\n| ISBN            = 979-1-18-932036-2\n| LicensedRelDate =\n| LicensedISBN    =\n| ChapterList     =\n}}\n{{Graphic novel list/footer}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://page.kakao.com/home?seriesId=50866481 Official webtoon website] in KakaoPage {{lang|ko}}\n\n[[Category:Manhwa titles]]\n[[Category:Webtoons in print]]\n[[Category:South Korean webtoons]]\n[[Category:Action webtoons]]\n[[Category:Fantasy webtoons]]\n\n{{Manhwa-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{italic title|noerror|string=Solo Leveling|all=yes}}\n{{Infobox novel\n|name       = Solo Leveling\n|author     = Chu-Gong\n|language   = Korean\n|country    = South Korea\n|genre      = Action, Fantasy\n|published  = Papyrus, [[KakaoPage]]\n|pub_date   = February 14, 2014; February 17, 2017 \u2013 October 10, 2018\n|media_type = Novel\n|isbn       = 1170336663\n}}\n{{Infobox manhwa\n| name_2       = Solo Leveling\n| image        = Solo Leveling Webtoon.png\n| hangul       = \ub098 \ud63c\uc790\ub9cc \ub808\ubca8\uc5c5\n| romanized    = Na Honjaman Level-up\n| genre        = Action, Fantasy\n| Adaptation   = \n| author       = Chu-Gong\n| illustrator  = Hyeon-Gun, Jang Sung-Rak\n| publisher    = D&C Media<!--The publisher for webtoon in print is D&C Media (\ub514\uc564\uc528\ubbf8\ub514\uc5b4). DO NOT use Kakao as the publisher.-->\n| magazine     = {{ubl|[[KakaoPage]] (South Korea)|[[Piccoma]] (Japan)}}\n| first        = 2018\n| firstmo      = March 4,\n| last         = 2020\n| volumes      = 2\n| chapter_list = \n| related      = \n}}\n'''Solo Leveling''' ({{Korean|hangul=\ub098 \ud63c\uc790\ub9cc \ub808\ubca8\uc5c5|rr=Na Honjaman Level-up|labels=yes}}) is a South [[Korean language|Korean]] novel written by Chu-Gong. It was serialized in Papyrus and later in [[Kakao]]'s media platform [[KakaoPage]] and concluded with 14 volumes and 270 chapters.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ipapyrus.co.kr/?document_srl=2545847|script-title=ko: :::\uafc8\uacfc \ud76c\ub9dd\uc774 \uc0b4\uc544\uc788\ub294 \ud30c\ud53c\ub8e8\uc2a4::: - \ub098 \ud63c\uc790\ub9cc \ub808\ubca8\uc5c5|website=Papyrus|access-date=August 5, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://page.kakao.com/home?seriesId=48787313|script-title=ko:\ub098 \ud63c\uc790\ub9cc \ub808\ubca8\uc5c5 [\uc644\uacb0]|last=\ucd94\uacf5|website=KakaoPage|language=ko|access-date=August 5, 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe webtoon adaptation has been serialized in KakaoPage since March 4, 2018, illustrated by Hyeon-gun and Jang Sung-Rak.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://page.kakao.com/home?seriesId=50866481|script-title=ko:\ub098 \ud63c\uc790\ub9cc \ub808\ubca8\uc5c5 [\ub3c5\uc810\uc5f0\uc7ac]|website=KakaoPage|language=ko|access-date=August 5, 2019}}</ref> The individual chapters collected and published by D&C Media into two volumes as of April 2020. ''Solo Leveling'' has been translated to many languages by way of [[fan translations]].\n\n== Plot ==\nSince a portal connecting our world to a world full of monsters and creatures of all kinds appeared, some people have acquired powers and the ability to hunt them: they are called hunters. The protagonist of the story, Sung Jin-Woo, is the weakest of the rank E hunters and barely stronger than a normal human. He is nicknamed by his fellow hunters as \"the weakest\". One day, he and other hunters find themselves trapped in an extremely dangerous dungeon, and only a few of them survive and manage to escape. Sung Jin-Woo himself hardly survives and is the only one who completes all the trials in this dungeon. He then turns into a \"player\" who can now see an interface showing him quests. Will he succeed in becoming the most powerful hunter?\n\nThe manhwa depicts how the weakest of all the hunters grows to become the strongest there is. Hunter Sung-Woo likes clearing dungeons alone and have gained tremendous strength and magic powers in the process. The Ant arc just finished and Sung Jin-Woo was able to defeat the Ant king without even using his full strength. The main antagonist of the manhwa seems to be a demon who is working from the shadows and we expect him to be the last and final boss in the journey of hunter Sung Jin-Woo leveling up.\n\n== Media ==\n<!--=== Novel volumes ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n!Vol.\n!Chapters\n|-\n|1\n|1 ~ 22\n|-\n|2\n|22 ~ 45\n|-\n|3\n|46 ~ 64\n|-\n|4\n|65 ~ 82\n|-\n|5\n|83 ~ 101\n|-\n|6\n|102 ~ 119\n|-\n|7\n|120 ~ 138\n|-\n|8\n|139 ~ 155\n|-\n|9\n|156 ~ 174\n|-\n|10\n|175 ~ 192\n|-\n|11\n|193 ~ 211\n|-\n|12\n|211 ~ 228\n|-\n|13\n|229 ~ 248\n|-\n|14\n|249 ~ 270\n|}\n-->\n===Manhwa===\n''Solo Leveling'' was launched in Kakao's webtoon platform [[KakaoPage]] on March 4, 2010. Its first [[trade paperback (comics)|collected volume]] was released by D&C Media on September 26, 2019.\n\n====Volume list====\n{{Graphic novel list/header\n| OneLanguage     = yes\n| Language        = Korean\n| Width           = 75%\n}}\n{{Graphic novel list\n| VolumeNumber    = 01\n| RelDate         = September 26, 2019<ref name=\"vol1\">{{cite web|url=https://book.naver.com/bookdb/book_detail.nhn?bid=15407921|script-title=ko:\ub098 \ud63c\uc790\ub9cc \ub808\ubca8\uc5c5 1|website=[[Naver|Naver Book Database]]|language=ko|access-date=April 23, 2020}}</ref>\n| ISBN            = 979-1-18-932029-4\n| LicensedRelDate =\n| LicensedISBN    =\n| ChapterList     =\n}}\n{{Graphic novel list\n| VolumeNumber    = 02\n| RelDate         = January 30, 2020<ref name=\"vol2\">{{cite web|url=https://book.naver.com/bookdb/book_detail.nhn?bid=16122656|script-title=ko:\ub098 \ud63c\uc790\ub9cc \ub808\ubca8\uc5c5 2|website=[[Naver|Naver Book Database]]|language=ko|access-date=April 23, 2020}}</ref>\n| ISBN            = 979-1-18-932036-2\n| LicensedRelDate =\n| LicensedISBN    =\n| ChapterList     =\n}}\n{{Graphic novel list/footer}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://page.kakao.com/home?seriesId=50866481 ''Solo Leveling''] in KakaoPage\n\n[[Category:Manhwa titles]]\n[[Category:Webtoons in print]]\n[[Category:South Korean webtoons]]\n[[Category:Action webtoons]]\n[[Category:Fantasy webtoons]]\n\n\n{{Manhwa-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Lord Yeager", "label": "safe", "comment": "Cleanup.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Solo_Leveling"}
