{"title_page": "Carlton best and fairest (AFL Women's)", "text_new": "{{Use Australian English|date=June 2018}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2018}}\n{{Infobox award\n| name        = Carlton best and fairest\n| image       = \n| imagesize   = \n| caption     =\n| description = The [[best and fairest]] player of the [[Carlton Football Club#AFL Women's team|Carlton Football Club]] in the [[AFL Women's]]\n| presenter   = [[Carlton Football Club#AFL Women's team|Carlton Football Club]]\n| country     = Australia\n| network     =\n| location    = \n| year        = 2017\n| year2       = \n| holder      = [[Madison Prespakis]]\n| website     = \n}}\n\nIn the [[AFL Women's]] (AFLW), the '''Carlton best and fairest''' award is awarded to the [[best and fairest]] player at the [[Carlton Football Club#AFL Women's team|Carlton Football Club]] during the home-and-away season. The award has been awarded annually since the competition's inaugural season in 2017, and [[Brianna Davey]] was the inaugural winner of the award.\n\n==Recipients==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n| '''Bold'''\n| Denotes current player\n|-\n| style=\"background:#D9F9E9\" |\n| Player won [[AFL Women's best and fairest]] in same season\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=text-align:center\n! Season\n! style=width:12em | Recipient(s)\n! class=unsortable | Ref.\n|-\n| [[2017 AFL Women's season|2017]] || style=\"text-align:left\" | '''{{sortname|Brianna|Davey}}''' || <ref>{{cite news|title=Davey crowned AFLW B&F|url=http://www.carltonfc.com.au/sites/Carlton/news/2017-04-27/davey-crowned-aflw-bf|work=carltonfc.com.au|date=27 April 2017|accessdate=19 June 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=2 | [[2018 AFL Women's season|2018]] || style=\"text-align:left\" | '''{{sortname|Katie|Loynes}}''' || rowspan=2 | <ref>{{cite news|last=Landsberger|first=Sam|title=Katie Loynes and Breann Moody crowed joint Carlton AFLW best-and-fairest winners|url=http://www.news.com.au/sport/afl/aflw/katie-loynes-and-breeann-moody-crowed-joint-carlton-aflw-bestandfairest-winners/news-story/b006e753f869b25491f1238e2b44932f|work=[[news.com.au]]|date=10 April 2018|accessdate=15 April 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\" | '''{{sortname|Breann|Moody}}'''\n|-\n| rowspan=2 | [[2019 AFL Women's season|2019]] || style=\"text-align:left\" | '''{{sortname|Brianna|Davey}}''' || rowspan=2 | <ref>{{cite news|title=First-year Blue ties with skipper to win best and fairest|url=https://womens.afl/news/17794/first-year-blue-ties-with-skipper-to-win-best-and-fairest|work=womens.afl|date=12 April 2019|accessdate=12 April 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\" | '''{{sortname|Madison|Prespakis}}'''\n|}\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Sports|Australia}}\n* [[John Nicholls Medal]] (list of Carlton Football Club best and fairest winners in the [[Australian Football League]])\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Carlton Football Club}}\n{{Carlton best and fairest (AFL Women's)}}\n{{AFL Women's best and fairest awards}}\n{{AFL Women's awards}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Carlton best and fairest (AFL Women's)}}\n[[Category:Australian rules football awards]]\n[[Category:AFL Women's]]\n[[Category:Carlton Football Club]]\n[[Category:Awards established in 2017]]\n[[Category:Australian rules football-related lists]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use Australian English|date=June 2018}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2018}}\n{{Infobox award\n| name        = Carlton best and fairest\n| image       = \n| imagesize   = \n| caption     =\n| description = The [[best and fairest]] player of the [[Carlton Football Club#AFL Women's team|Carlton Football Club]] in the [[AFL Women's]]\n| presenter   = [[Carlton Football Club#AFL Women's team|Carlton Football Club]]\n| country     = Australia\n| network     =\n| location    = \n| year        = 2017\n| year2       = \n| holder      = [[Brianna Davey]]<br>[[Madison Prespakis]]\n| website     = \n}}\n\nIn the [[AFL Women's]] (AFLW), the '''Carlton best and fairest''' award is awarded to the [[best and fairest]] player at the [[Carlton Football Club#AFL Women's team|Carlton Football Club]] during the home-and-away season. The award has been awarded annually since the competition's inaugural season in 2017, and [[Brianna Davey]] was the inaugural winner of the award.\n\n==Recipients==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n| '''Bold'''\n| Denotes current player\n|-\n| style=\"background:#D9F9E9\" |\n| Player won [[AFL Women's best and fairest]] in same season\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=text-align:center\n! Season\n! style=width:12em | Recipient(s)\n! class=unsortable | Ref.\n|-\n| [[2017 AFL Women's season|2017]] || style=\"text-align:left\" | '''{{sortname|Brianna|Davey}}''' || <ref>{{cite news|title=Davey crowned AFLW B&F|url=http://www.carltonfc.com.au/sites/Carlton/news/2017-04-27/davey-crowned-aflw-bf|work=carltonfc.com.au|date=27 April 2017|accessdate=19 June 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=2 | [[2018 AFL Women's season|2018]] || style=\"text-align:left\" | '''{{sortname|Katie|Loynes}}''' || rowspan=2 | <ref>{{cite news|last=Landsberger|first=Sam|title=Katie Loynes and Breann Moody crowed joint Carlton AFLW best-and-fairest winners|url=http://www.news.com.au/sport/afl/aflw/katie-loynes-and-breeann-moody-crowed-joint-carlton-aflw-bestandfairest-winners/news-story/b006e753f869b25491f1238e2b44932f|work=[[news.com.au]]|date=10 April 2018|accessdate=15 April 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\" | '''{{sortname|Breann|Moody}}'''\n|-\n| rowspan=2 | [[2019 AFL Women's season|2019]] || style=\"text-align:left\" | '''{{sortname|Brianna|Davey}}''' || rowspan=2 | <ref>{{cite news|title=First-year Blue ties with skipper to win best and fairest|url=https://womens.afl/news/17794/first-year-blue-ties-with-skipper-to-win-best-and-fairest|work=womens.afl|date=12 April 2019|accessdate=12 April 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\" | '''{{sortname|Madison|Prespakis}}'''\n|}\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Sports|Australia}}\n* [[John Nicholls Medal]] (list of Carlton Football Club best and fa